  "prompt": "Is there a realistic alternative to plastic?",
  "response": "Several promising alternatives to traditional plastics exist:\n\n1. Biodegradable materials\n- PLA (corn-based plastic)\n- Mushroom-based packaging\n- Seaweed-based packaging\n- Hemp plastics\n\n2. Sustainable plant-based materials\n- Bamboo\n- Cellulose\n- Agricultural waste derivatives\n\n3. Recyclable alternatives\n- Glass\n- Metal containers\n- Paper and cardboard\n- Silicone\n\n4. Advanced bio-based materials\n- Algae-based plastics\n- Mycelium (fungus-based materials)\n- Bacterial cellulose\n\n5. Advanced synthetic alternatives\n- Bioplastics\n- Plant-based polymers\n- Compostable plastics\n\n6. Natural materials\n- Wood\n- Stone\n- Clay\n\nEach alternative has pros and cons regarding:\n- Production cost\n- Environmental impact\n- Durability\n- Scalability\n- Performance characteristics\n\nNo single material perfectly replaces plastic in all applications, but ongoing research continues to develop more sustainable options. The most effective approach often involves using multiple materials strategically based on specific use cases.\n\nThe best alternatives depend on the specific application, balancing environmental concerns with practical requirements.",
